						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up by the side of the central shrine in Lakshmīnārāyaṇadēva temple.</p>						

						<p>Circa 13th century.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record registers a gift, for burning a perpetual lamp and supplying flower garlands in the temple of Lakshmīnārāyaṇadēva. It refers to Bārakūru. All other details are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
